column10: Cholesterol: Understanding Levels and Numbers (clevelandclinic.org)
column12: The total cholesterol in mg/dL (LBXTC) was converted to mmol/L (LBDTCSI) by multiplying by 0.02586.
Triglycerides were measured in a fasting subsample of participants 12 years and older. Special sample weights are required to analyze these data properly.

column10: Triglycerides: Levels & Normal Range (clevelandclinic.org)
column12: The triglycerides value in mg/dL (LBXTR) was converted to mmol/L (LBDTRSI) by multiplying by 0.01129.
The calculation is valid for triglycerides less than or equal to 400 mg/dL.

column10: Cholesterol: Understanding Levels and Numbers (clevelandclinic.org)
column12: [LDL-cholesterol] = [total cholesterol] – [HDL-cholesterol] – [triglycerides/5]
The LDL-cholesterol in mg/dL (LBDLDL) was converted to mmol/L (LBDLDLSI) by multiplying by 0.02586.
